{"title_page": "Ministry of Healthcare (Azerbaijan)", "text_new": "{{Infobox government agency\n|agency_name     = Ministry of Healthcare of Azerbaijan Republic\n|nativename      = Az\u0259rbaycan Respublikas\u0131n\u0131n S\u0259hiyy\u0259 Nazirliyi\n|nativename_a    =\n|nativename_r    =\n|logo            =\n|logo_width      =\n|logo_caption    =\n|seal            = Coat of arms of Azerbaijan.svg\n|seal_width      = 120px\n|seal_caption    = Coat of arms of Azerbaijan\n|formed          = June 17, 1918\n|date1           = \n|date1_name      = \n|date2           = \n|date2_name      =\n|preceding1      = \n|preceding2      = \n|dissolved       =\n|superseding     =\n|jurisdiction    =\n|headquarters    = 4 Ki\u00e7ik D\u0259niz Street, [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijan Republic]] AZ1014\n|latd            = \n|latm            = \n|lats            = \n|latNS           = \n|longd           = \n|longm           =\n|longs           = \n|longEW          = \n|employees       = \n|budget          = \n|chief1_name     = [[Ogtay Shiraliyev]] \n|chief1_position = <br>Minister of Healthcare\n|chief2_name     = \n|chief2_position = \n|chief3_name     = \n|chief3_position = \n|parent_agency   =\n|child1_agency   = \n|child2_agency   =\n|website         = [http://www.sehiyye.gov.az/ www.sehiyye.gov.az]\n|footnotes       =\n}}\n[[File:Az\u0259rbaycan Respublikas\u0131 S\u0259hiyy\u0259 Nazirliyinin binas\u0131 30.12.2011.jpg|thumb|220px|Ministry of Health of Azerbaijan Republic]]\nThe '''Ministry of Healthcare of Azerbaijan Republic''', also known as '''Ministry of Health of Azerbaijan Republic''' ({{lang-az|'''Az\u0259rbaycan Respublikas\u0131n\u0131n S\u0259hiyy\u0259 Nazirliyi'''}}) is a [[governmental agency]] within the [[Cabinet of Azerbaijan]] in charge of regulating the healthcare system in [[Azerbaijan Republic]]. The ministry is headed by [[Ogtay Shiraliyev]].<ref name=CIA>{{cite web|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/world-leaders-1/world-leaders-a/azerbaijan.html |title=CIA. Chiefs of State and Cabinet Members of Foreign Governments |accessdate=2010-11-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100528054345/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/world-leaders-1/world-leaders-a/azerbaijan.html |archivedate=2010-05-28 }}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe Ministry of Healthcare was established on June 17, 1918 by the decree of Council of Ministers of [[Azerbaijan Democratic Republic]] led by [[Fatali Khan Khoyski]]. The first appointed minister was [[Khudadat Rafibeyli]], who had graduated from [[Kharkov University]] in 1903 and was the most experienced surgeon in the country at the time.\nThe ministry consisted of five departments, including city healthcare department, healthcare statistics, therapy, rural healthcare and veterinary offices. The medical care was provided to the population free of charge while the authorities built new hospitals, laboratories, medicine warehouses and purchased medical equipment.\nThroughout the 23-month-long existence of Azerbaijan Democratic Republic, 33 hospitals operated in Azerbaijani provinces with each having 1 doctor, 2 paramedics, 1 gynecologist and one nurse conducting vaccinations. According to statistics, there was only one doctor per every 75,000 citizens. Due to the shortage, the [[National Assembly of Azerbaijan|Azerbaijani parliament]] included building of 35 new hospitals and 56 paramedical office in 1920 fiscal budget committing [[Azerbaijani manat|AZN]] 43,321,950. During the Soviet rule of Azerbaijan, new hospitals and pharmacies were built. State pharmacy and analytical laboratories was established in Baku in order to prepare medicines, bacteriological drugs, syrups and investigate medical records during the issues relating with crime. In 1960-70s, the medical sector was enhanced and new ambulance services opened for public.\nThe ministry today operates under statute signed by [[President of Azerbaijan|President]] [[Heydar Aliyev]] on December 29, 1998.<ref name=Min>{{cite web |url=http://azerbaijan.tourism.az/index.php?/az/topmenu_content/1111 |title=S\u0259hiyy\u0259 Nazirliyi |trans-title=Ministry of Healthcare |accessdate=2010-11-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120707072214/http://azerbaijan.tourism.az/index.php?/az/topmenu_content/1111 |archivedate=2012-07-07 }}</ref>\n\n== The statute of the Ministry of Health ==\nThe presidential decree was signed on May 25, 2006 by Azerbaijani president [[Ilham Aliyev]] and covers issues such as the structure and other issues relating with the Ministry of Health of Azerbaijan. Other two statutes accepted in 1998 and 2005 were invalidated after the acceptance of new statute numbered 413. In accordance with the statute the structure of the ministry was submitted and staff of the chairmanship was defined as 87 people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sehiyye.gov.az/sehiyye-nazirliyinin-esasnamesi.html|title=S\u0259hiyy\u0259 Nazirliyinin \u018fsasnam\u0259si|website=www.sehiyye.gov.az|access-date=2019-06-29}}</ref>\n\n==Structure==\nMain functions of the ministry are organization and regulation of healthcare system in the country to provide sufficient medical care to the population; preparation and implementation of state healthcare programs; conduct activities for improvement of services by medical companies in both state and private sector; regulation of sanitary-epidemiology stations in the country; preparation of programs on parenthood and family planning; provision of medical drugs, bacteriological and antivirus products to hospitals; regulations and development of pharmacy offices networks; research and development of medical equipment manufacturing; prevention of dangerous diseases in the country and so forth.<ref name=Min/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mednet.az/index.htm |title=Az\u0259rbaycan Respublikas\u0131n\u0131n S\u0259hiyy\u0259 Nazirliyi |trans-title=Ministry of Healthcare of Azerbaijan Republic |accessdate=2010-11-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101229074210/http://www.mednet.az/index.htm |archivedate=2010-12-29 }}</ref>\n\n== International relations ==\nIn order of improvement of healthcare in the country, Ministry of Healthcare Azerbaijan cooperates with a number of international organizations and shares experiences with foreign countries.\n\n=== Rostrapovich-Vishnevskaya Foundation ===\nDuring the years of 2010-2012 the Ministry of Healthcare of Azerbaijan cooperated with [[Rostropovich-Vishnevskaya Foundation|Rostrapovich-Vishnevskaya Foundation]]. Parties signed an agreement on \u201cDiagnosis of pregnant women against HepB and [[HIV]] viruses and prevention of newborn against HepB.\u201d At the same time, ministry organized an immunization campaign and vaccine program with support of foundation. As a result, indications of the diseases such as [[measles]], [[mumps]] and parotid decreased in the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sehiyye.gov.az/xeberler/10-shiyy-naziri-oqtay-irliyev-rostrapovi-vinevskaya-fondunun-prezidenti-yelena-rostrapovii-qbul-edib.html|title=S\u0259hiyy\u0259 naziri Oqtay \u015eir\u0259liyev Rostrapovi\u00e7-Vi\u015fnevskaya Fondunun prezidenti Yelena Rostrapovi\u00e7i q\u0259bul edib|website=sehiyye.gov.az|access-date=2019-02-28}}</ref>\n\n=== World Health Organization ===\nSince 2006 Ministry of Healthcare Azerbaijan has been represented on European Region\u2019s Standing Committee of the Regional Committee and twice on WHO\u2019s Executive Board. 61st session of the WHO Regional Committee for Europe was held in Azerbaijan in 2011. During the meeting public health experts and ministers of health from 53 countries signed an agreement relating to the public health problems and current health threats in European region. At the same time, Health 2020 \u2013 a new European Health Policy Framework was also discussed during the session and accepted Sustainable Development Agenda 2030. Country office of the [[World Health Organization]] in Azerbaijan was established in June 1994 in Baku. The office carries out implementation of WHO programs in the country with staff consists of six people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sehiyye.gov.az/xeberler/24-shiyy-naziri-oqtay-irliyev-st-t-avropa-regional-komitsinin-60-c-sessiyasnda-itirak-edib.html|title=S\u0259hiyy\u0259 naziri Oqtay \u015eir\u0259liyev \u00dcST-t\u0131 Avropa Regional Komit\u0259sinin 60-c\u0131 sessiyas\u0131nda i\u015ftirak edib|website=sehiyye.gov.az|access-date=2019-02-28}}</ref>\n\nSince 2006 Azerbaijan has started HIV treatment services in the country with the support of WHO. Current prior programs are carried out in the field of healthcare such as, noncommunicable diseases, maternal and child health, health system strengthening, tuberculosis, immunization and tobacco control.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://unazerbaijan.org/en/un_agencies/world-health-organization/|title=World Health Organization (WHO) \u2013 United Nations Azerbaijan|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-28}}</ref>\n\n=== Organization of Islamic Cooperation ===\nMinistry of Healthcare Azerbaijan cooperates with the member countries of [[Organisation of Islamic Cooperation|OIC]] and participates in sessions of ministries of health. The third Islamic Conference of Ministries of Health was held in [[Kazakhstan]] on September 29, 2011. The minister of healthcare Oktay Shiraliyev also participated in three days last session. Ministers of health from 53 member countries and representatives from international organizations participated in the meeting. During the session discussions were carried out relating to the developments and cooperative works between member countries, prevention of infectious and non-infectious diseases and improving the potential of health workers and equipment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sehiyye.gov.az/xeberler/329-shiyy-naziri-oqtay-irliyev-slam-mkdalq-tkilat-shiyy-nazirlrinin-3-c-sessiyasnda-itirak-etmidir.html|title=S\u0259hiyy\u0259 Naziri Oqtay \u015eir\u0259liyev \u0130slam \u018fm\u0259kda\u015fl\u0131q T\u0259\u015fkilat\u0131 S\u0259hiyy\u0259 Nazirl\u0259rinin 3-c\u00fc sessiyas\u0131nda i\u015ftirak etmi\u015fdir|website=sehiyye.gov.az|access-date=2019-02-28}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Cabinet of Azerbaijan]]\n*[[Healthcare in Azerbaijan]]\n*[[Azerbaijan Medical University|Azerbaijan State Medical University]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Ministries of Azerbaijan}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ministry of Healthcare (Azerbaijan)}}\n[[Category:Government ministries of Azerbaijan|Healthcare]]\n[[Category:Health ministries|Azerbaijan]]\n[[Category:Ministries established in 1918|Azerbaijan, Healthcare]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox government agency\n|agency_name     = Ministry of Healthcare of Azerbaijan Republic\n|nativename      = Az\u0259rbaycan Respublikas\u0131n\u0131n S\u0259hiyy\u0259 Nazirliyi\n|nativename_a    =\n|nativename_r    =\n|logo            =\n|logo_width      =\n|logo_caption    =\n|seal            = Coat of arms of Azerbaijan.svg\n|seal_width      = 120px\n|seal_caption    = Coat of arms of Azerbaijan\n|formed          = June 17, 1918\n|date1           = \n|date1_name      = \n|date2           = \n|date2_name      =\n|preceding1      = \n|preceding2      = \n|dissolved       =\n|superseding     =\n|jurisdiction    =\n|headquarters    = 4 Ki\u00e7ik D\u0259niz Street, [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijan Republic]] AZ1014\n|latd            = \n|latm            = \n|lats            = \n|latNS           = \n|longd           = \n|longm           =\n|longs           = \n|longEW          = \n|employees       = \n|budget          = \n|chief1_name     = [[Ogtay Shiraliyev]] \n|chief1_position = <br>Minister of Healthcare\n|chief2_name     = \n|chief2_position = \n|chief3_name     = \n|chief3_position = \n|parent_agency   =\n|child1_agency   = \n|child2_agency   =\n|website         = [http://www.sehiyye.gov.az/ www.sehiyye.gov.az]\n|footnotes       =\n}}\n[[File:Az\u0259rbaycan Respublikas\u0131 S\u0259hiyy\u0259 Nazirliyinin binas\u0131 30.12.2011.jpg|