egional Committee and twice on WHO\u2019s Executive Board. 61st session of the WHO Regional Committee for Europe was held in Azerbaijan in 2011. During the meeting public health experts and ministers of health from 53 countries signed an agreement relating to the public health problems and current health threats in European region. At the same time, Health 2020 \u2013 a new European Health Policy Framework was also discussed during the session and accepted Sustainable Development Agenda 2030. Country office of the [[World Health Organization]] in Azerbaijan was established in June 1994 in Baku. The office carries out implementation of WHO programs in the country with staff consists of six people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sehiyye.gov.az/xeberler/24-shiyy-naziri-oqtay-irliyev-st-t-avropa-regional-komitsinin-60-c-sessiyasnda-itirak-edib.html|title=S\u0259hiyy\u0259 naziri Oqtay \u015eir\u0259liyev \u00dcST-t\u0131 Avropa Regional Komit\u0259sinin 60-c\u0131 sessiyas\u0131nda i\u015ftirak edib|website=sehiyye.gov.az|access-date=2019-02-28}}</ref>\n\nSince 2006 Azerbaijan has started HIV treatment services in the country with the support of WHO. Current prior programs are carried out in the field of healthcare such as, noncommunicable diseases, maternal and child health, health system strengthening, tuberculosis, immunization and tobacco control.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://unazerbaijan.org/en/un_agencies/world-health-organization/|title=World Health Organization (WHO) \u2013 United Nations Azerbaijan|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-28}}</ref>\n\n=== Organization of Islamic Cooperation ===\nMinistry of Healthcare Azerbaijan cooperates with the member countries of [[Organisation of Islamic Cooperation|OIC]] and participates in sessions of ministries of health. The third Islamic Conference of Ministries of Health was held in [[Kazakhstan]] on September 29, 2011. The minister of healthcare Oktay Shiraliyev was also participated in three days last session. Ministers of health from 53 member countries and representatives from international organizations participated in the meeting. During the session discussions were carried out relating to the developments and cooperative works between member countries, prevention of infectious and non-infectious diseases and improving the potential of health workers and equipment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sehiyye.gov.az/xeberler/329-shiyy-naziri-oqtay-irliyev-slam-mkdalq-tkilat-shiyy-nazirlrinin-3-c-sessiyasnda-itirak-etmidir.html|title=S\u0259hiyy\u0259 Naziri Oqtay \u015eir\u0259liyev \u0130slam \u018fm\u0259kda\u015fl\u0131q T\u0259\u015fkilat\u0131 S\u0259hiyy\u0259 Nazirl\u0259rinin 3-c\u00fc sessiyas\u0131nda i\u015ftirak etmi\u015fdir|website=sehiyye.gov.az|access-date=2019-02-28}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Cabinet of Azerbaijan]]\n*[[Healthcare in Azerbaijan]]\n*[[Azerbaijan Medical University|Azerbaijan State Medical University]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Ministries of Azerbaijan}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ministry of Healthcare (Azerbaijan)}}\n[[Category:Government ministries of Azerbaijan|Healthcare]]\n[[Category:Health ministries|Azerbaijan]]\n[[Category:Ministries established in 1918|Azerbaijan, Healthcare]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eOrganization of Islamic Cooperation:Grammar fixing, replaced: was also participated \u2192 also participated", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_Healthcare_(Azerbaijan)"}
